African Tea Prices Rise For Second Week at Auction in Port City of Mombasa

-- B y   A l a s t a i r   R e e d
-- 
2011-06-08T07:06:38Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-08/african-tea-prices-rise-for-second-week-at-auction-in-port-city-of-mombasa.html
African tea prices rose for a second
week at a sale in the Kenyan port city of  Mombasa , according to
Tea Brokers East Africa Ltd. said.  Prices increased to an average of $2.65 per kilogram (2.2
pounds) from $2.63 a week earlier, the broker said in an e-
mailed report today.  For Related News and Information:  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Alastair Reed at 
 areed12@bloomberg.net  